    stem: `A 20-year-old woman presents to your clinic because she has never had a period. On examination, the genitalia appear completely normal. The breasts are immature, but pubic and axillary hair are present. Pelvic ultrasound shows a normal uterus and fallopian tubes, but the ovaries contain a small amount of connective tissue and no follicles. Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her amenorrhea?`,
