    subtopic: "Drug interactions with oral contraceptives - Carbamazepine and contraception",
    stem: `A 24-year-old woman is at your office for a prescription for oral contraceptive pills. She has a history of epilepsy for the past five years and is on carbamazepine. She has not had any episodes of seizures in the past six months. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate advice?`,
