    subtopic: "Menopausal vasomotor symptoms in breast cancer survivors",
    stem: `A 58-year-old woman presents to your practice with complaints of hot flashes and mood swings for the past 12 months. Her menstrual periods ceased 2 years ago. She has a history of breast cancer at the age of 35 that was treated successfully. Which one of the following is the most appropriate management for her symptoms?`,
